==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: offset printing
<hw>off"set print"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Printing)</fld> <def>A
printing technique in which a lithographic image on an inked metal or
stone plate is transferred first to a rubber sheet (usually on a
cylinder) before transfer to the paper. Called also <altname>offset
lithography</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>offsetting</ent>⟦br⟧
